Flask API with SQLAlchemy and Elasticsearch Integration

Run ./setup.sh to start the server 


Access the API at http://localhost:8085

default user:password = admin:password

Endpoints


Health Check
Endpoint: /health
Method: GET
Description: Returns a success message to indicate the health of the API.
User Endpoints


Get All Users:

Endpoint: /api/v1/user
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves information about all users.
Get Single User:

Endpoint: /api/v1/user/<username>
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves information about a specific user.
Create User:

Endpoint: /api/v1/user
Method: POST
Description: Creates a new user. Requires JSON payload with username and password.



List Items:

Endpoint: /api/v1/item
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves all items from the Elasticsearch index.
Default list of products is nothing /NULL


Index Document:
Endpoint: /api/v1/item
Method: POST
Description: Indexes a new document in Elasticsearch. Requires a JSON payload.


